{"lemma":"كَبِيسٍ","slug":"كَبِيسٍ","root":"ك.ب.س","root_slug":"ك-ب-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ب-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36599"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B3%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"preserved; pickled, canned, bottled etc."},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"preserved; stuffed, mummified"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"preserved; intercalary, leap … (as in leap year)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pickles","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ك ب س (k b s), but the “intercalary” meaning is a semantic loan from Classical Syriac ܟܒܝܫ (kabbīš), the passive participle of ܟܒܰܫ (kḇaš, “to tread down”), the Syriac verb corresponding to Arabic كَبَسَ (kabasa, “to press down”)."},"ipa":["/ka.biːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36599","headword_ar":"كَبِيسٌ","root":"kbs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the best kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) thus called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when dry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but when fresh, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u jiro*aAnK","text_ar":"اُمُّ جِرْذَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is also the name of the tree that bears them. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of women's ornament, made hollow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and coated with perfume,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffed with perfume,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then worn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a necklace being made of ornaments of this kind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~anapu Alkabiysapu","text_ar":"السَّنَةُ الكَبِيسَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAmu Alkabiysi","text_ar":"عَامُ الكَبِيسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Az, in TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subaATN","text_ar":"سُبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The intercalary year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leap-year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"both in the Syrian, or Julian, reckoning, and in the Coptic;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the year from which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohaA","text_ar":"مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) accord. to the S and K, but properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahaA","text_ar":"لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) as in the work entitled"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawolu AlmaA^onuwsu","text_ar":"القَوْلُ المَاْنُوسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a day is stolen"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yusotaraqu","text_ar":"يُسْتَرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and intercalated"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"once"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in every four years;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the S and K; for the said day is an addition thereto; (MF, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the year in which the Syrians following the Greeks, add a day to the month"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subaAT","text_ar":"سُبَاط"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which corresponds to February, O. S.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making it twentynine days instead of twenty-eight, which they do once in four years;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that in which the Copts intercalate, at the end, six epagomenæ instead of five, which, in like manner, they do once in every four years."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","A","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}